    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between HSS, cobalt and carbide drill bits?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>HSS (High Speed Steel)</strong> is the standard material for general-purpose drilling in mild steel, aluminium and plastics. <strong>Cobalt (HSS-E)</strong> contains 5-8% cobalt for improved heat resistance — ideal for stainless steel and harder metals. <strong>Solid carbide</strong> is the hardest and most wear-resistant, suited to high-volume production and CNC machining at higher speeds.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I choose the right tap for thread cutting?",
            "answer": "<p>Consider three factors: <strong>material</strong> (HSS for mild steel, HSS-E for stainless), <strong>hole type</strong> (spiral flute for blind holes, spiral point for through holes, straight flute for general purpose), and <strong>thread form</strong> (metric coarse M, metric fine MF, or BSP/BSW for pipe and legacy threads). For hand tapping, use a set of taper, second and bottoming taps.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What do drill bit coatings like TiN and TiAlN do?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>TiN (Titanium Nitride)</strong> is the gold-coloured coating that increases surface hardness and reduces friction, extending tool life by up to 3x in steel. <strong>TiAlN (Titanium Aluminium Nitride)</strong> offers higher heat resistance for faster cutting speeds and is ideal for stainless steel and harder alloys. Uncoated HSS is suitable for softer metals and general-purpose work.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Dormer the same as Dormer Pramet?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Dormer Pramet</strong> was formed in 2014 by merging Dormer Tools (founded 1913 in Sheffield) with the Pramet brand. Both are part of the <strong>Sandvik Group</strong>. Dormer products focus on rotary tools — drill bits, taps, dies, end mills and reamers — while Pramet covers indexable inserts and toolholders. Both brands are now united under the Dormer Pramet name.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What drill bit do I need for stainless steel?",
            "answer": "<p>For stainless steel, use a <strong>cobalt (HSS-E) drill bit</strong> with a 135-degree split point. Cobalt's superior heat resistance prevents the work-hardening that causes standard HSS bits to fail in stainless. For higher volumes, consider a <strong>TiAlN-coated solid carbide</strong> drill. Use a slow speed, steady feed rate and cutting fluid for best results.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Dormer cutting tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Dormer range including drill bits, taps, dies and end mills. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. Free next-day delivery on all orders over £99.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
